The paper deals with the capacity bounds of wireless networks with unknown channel parameters, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of relays and training in the network suggests that it may also fall under the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also discusses optimal signaling structures and achievability strategies, which could fall under the signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the trade-off between channel learning and communication, which could fall under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
